http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Vivekananda%E2%80%99s-teachings-are-relevant%E2%80%99/article14000512.ece

Visvesvaraya Technological University has taken up social service programmes to mark the celebration of Youth Week on the occasion of Swami Vivekananda’s birth anniversary.As part of these programmes, a special lecture was organised on Thursday where social worker Alka Inamdar said that Swami Vivekananda’s teachings were relevant for the contemporary society as divisive forces were working to weaken India.D.H. Rao, executive council member of VTU, said that the youth should strive hard to acquire the latest knowledge in their chosen subjects and acquire skills.